    {
      "slideNumber": 4,
      "title": "What is Divide and Conquer?",
      "content": [
        "Divide and Conquer is an algorithm design paradigm based on multi-branched recursion.",
        "It works by breaking down a problem into three distinct steps:",
        "Divide: Break the given problem into smaller sub-problems of the same type.",
        "Conquer: Recursively solve these sub-problems. (If the sub-problem is small enough, solve it directly as a base case).",
        "Combine: Appropriately combine the answers of the sub-problems to get the exact solution to the original problem."
      ],
      "ocrContent": "",
      "notes": "",
      "images": [],
      "isTextLight": false,
      "isScreenshot": false
    },
