      "title": "Merge sort time Analysis",
      "content": [
        "In the divide part the main array of size n is divided into two equal arrays",
        "In the conquer array you almost makes n comparisons in total so the recurrent relationship can be written as follows",
        "T(n)=2T(n/2) +n T(1)=1",
        "After solving it the T(n)= n + n log(n) which is  θ ( nlogn )",
        "This is faster than other sorting algorithms"
      ],
      "ocrContent": "",
      "notes": "",
