    {
      "slideNumber": 79,
      "title": "Binary Tree Traversal",
      "content": [
        "It one of important topic in divide and conquer it is used in different application such as compliers (parse trees) and filing system",
        "Tree traversal is the process of visiting each node in a tree data structure, exactly once, in a systematic manner",
        "It has three different types methods:",
        "Preorder:  the root is visited before the left and right subtrees are visited (in that order).",
        "Inorder : the root is visited after visiting its left subtree but before visiting the right subtree.",
        "Postorder : the root is visited after visiting the left and right subtrees (in that order)."
      ],
      "ocrContent": "",
      "notes": "",
